 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S5-P02-T060 (exact + structured retrieval; NOT_DEPLOYED)
+
+- Sixtieth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program, opening S5-P02 (exact, structured, full-text and historical retrieval). Delivers the deterministic retrieval benefit a professional user needs first: look up a document by its exact 文号 or DOI and get it as the first result every time, and filter by agency/region/date-range/status with results identical to a SQL baseline. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; a retrieval library, the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/exact_search.py provides build_index (exact hash indexes on doc_number and doi plus facet indexes on agency/region/status), exact_lookup (the first, and only, result for an exact identifier, with a normalized match so spacing/case never misses), and structured_filter (facet AND plus an inclusive date range). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S5-P02-T060/: corpus.json (a 120-document test corpus), search_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND; verifier strengthened: real ASCII-letter DOI case-fold + real-date boundary queries). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S5-P02-T060/test-results/search_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): the test corpus has 120 documents with 120 distinct document numbers and doc_ids; 100 exact identifiers each return the correct document as the first result for a 100% hit rate, and all 24 DOIs also hit, including a spaced/upper-case DOI via normalization; and structured_filter agrees with a real SQL baseline (an in-memory sqlite3 query with the equivalent WHERE clause) across 38 queries (single facets, combinations, date ranges) with 0 mismatches, compared as ordered lists, with the battery non-vacuous (a facet genuinely filters). Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S5-P01-T059 (cross-board Evidence Relation; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Fifty-ninth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S5-P01), closing S5-P01. Connects the boards -- policy, papers, standards, patents, statistics, pilots, procurement -- but does not build a boundless knowledge graph: relations follow a bounded vocabulary and every saved relation must carry document + fragment evidence. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; a relation layer, the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/evidence_relation.py provides RELATION_TYPES (a fixed predicate vocabulary with allowed subject-kind/object-kind pairs), add_relation (refuse an off-vocabulary relation or an unknown board kind; save only with document + fragment evidence; otherwise return an explicitly-marked inferred_unsaved record that is NOT stored as a fact), build_graph, and query. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S5-P01-T059/: relation_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND; evidence rule hardened to also strip doc_id). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S5-P01-T059/test-results/relation_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): 7 assertions resolve to 4 saved relations, 2 refused, and 1 inferred_unsaved; every saved relation carries a source document id and a non-empty supporting fragment (using real backfilled document numbers such as 苏政办函〔2026〕39号 with realistic quoted fragments), and the graph contains exactly those evidence-backed edges; an assertion with no evidence is explicitly marked inferred_unsaved and never enters the graph; and the graph is bounded, since an off-vocabulary relation (a paper implementing a policy) and an unknown board kind (a tweet) are both refused. Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
